* Investigate\nShuffle Issues
** What is Shuffle
***_ Data moves between nodes
***_ During joins, aggregations
***_ Serialize → disk → network
***_ Expensive operation
** Identify in Spark UI
***_ Shuffle Read column
***_ Shuffle Write column
***_ Large values = excessive movement
***_ DAG: Exchange nodes
** Reduce Shuffle
***_ Filter data early
***_ Use broadcast joins (<30MB)
***_ AQE auto-converts when possible
***_ Avoid unnecessary repartition()
** Broadcast Joins
***_ One small table in memory
***_ No shuffle required
***_ AQE detects at runtime
** Colocation
***_ Bucket/partition similarly
***_ Tables joined on same key
***_ Minimize cross-node transfer
@endmindmap
